[{"command_name": "Plan.append_task", "args": {"task_id": "1", "dependent_task_ids": [], "instruction": "Implement the following in Python 3 and save the file to /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/find_zero.py. The file must contain ONLY the proper import(s) and these two function implementations (no tests, no prints, no execution code). Ensure the file is written to disk and verify its existence before reporting completion.\n\nCode to write:\n\nimport math\n\ndef poly(xs: list, x: float) -> float:\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\n    Evaluates polynomial with coefficients xs at point x.\n    return xs[0] + xs[1] * x + xs[2] * x^2 + ... + xs[n] * x^n\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\n    # Horner's method for efficiency and numerical stability\n    result = 0.0\n    for coeff in reversed(xs):\n        result = result * x + coeff\n    return result\n\ndef find_zero(xs: list) -> float:\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\n    xs are coefficients of a polynomial.\n    find_zero finds x such that poly(xs, x) = 0.\n    find_zero returns only one zero point, even if there are many.\n    Moreover, find_zero only takes list xs having even number of coefficients\n    and largest non zero coefficient as it guarantees a solution.\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\n    if not xs:\n        raise ValueError(\\\"xs must be non-empty\\\")\n    if len(xs) % 2 != 0:\n        raise ValueError(\\\"xs must have an even number of coefficients\\\")\n    if xs[-1] == 0:\n        raise ValueError(\\\"highest-degree coefficient must be non-zero\\\")\n\n    # Bracket a root by expanding interval symmetrically (odd-degree implies a real root)\n    a, b = -1.0, 1.0\n    fa = poly(xs, a)\n    fb = poly(xs, b)\n    k = 0\n    while fa * fb > 0:\n        k += 1\n        a *= 2.0\n        b *= 2.0\n        fa = poly(xs, a)\n        fb = poly(xs, b)\n        if k > 60:\n            break\n    if fa == 0.0:\n        return a\n    if fb == 0.0:\n        return b\n\n    # Bisection to locate one root\n    for _ in range(200):\n        m = 0.5 * (a + b)\n